Subject: [PATCH] Fix hicum2 C++ name mangling issue

The hicum2ext.h header was missing extern "C" guards, causing C++
name mangling when included from C++ files. This resulted in linking
errors because the actual function implementations in C files have
C linkage.

This patch adds the necessary extern "C" guards to ensure all
function declarations in hicum2ext.h use C linkage regardless of
whether they're included from C or C++ code.
---
 src/spicelib/devices/hicum2/hicum2ext.h | 7 +++++++
 1 file changed, 7 insertions(+)

--- a/src/spicelib/devices/hicum2/hicum2ext.h
+++ b/src/spicelib/devices/hicum2/hicum2ext.h
@@ -6,6 +6,9 @@
 #ifndef __HICUMEXT_H
 #define __HICUMEXT_H

+#ifdef __cplusplus
+extern "C" {
+#endif

 extern int HICUMacLoad(GENmodel *,CKTcircuit*);
 extern int HICUMask(CKTcircuit *,GENinstance*,int,IFvalue*,IFvalue*);
@@ -30,4 +33,8 @@
 extern int HICUMbindCSCComplexToReal (GENmodel*, CKTcircuit*) ;
 #endif

+#ifdef __cplusplus
+}
+#endif
+
 #endif
